yment or Service, but modifying the Ingress is fine since that's a separate resource. Creating new resources like the `ingress-gateway` Service is also allowed.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what the agent actually needs to do: check the current state of the demo-app ingress, see what controllers are available, and determine whether I need to deploy a second controller or if I can work with what's already there.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2761,"cache_read_input_tokens":43905,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2761},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dd5b4f2f-800f-4b87-9365-c0b47e6cd0e8","uuid":"a4a8c508-e6df-4595-bad3-aa6e5b727117","request_id":"req_011CcQ4E3wrraR71Cb7tQSRp"}
